cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SP, cs.AI 

The paper deals with the reconstruction of compressively measured images using phase-only filtering. This involves techniques from computer vision (cs.CV) for image processing, information theory (cs.IT) for compressive sensing, multimedia (cs.MM) for image compression, signal processing (cs.SP) for filtering, and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for pattern recognition. Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories in order of relevance.
